{"lemma":"رَجَزِ","slug":"رَجَزِ","root":"ر.ج.ز","root_slug":"ر-ج-ز","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ج-ز","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"رَجَزِ","root":"رجز","pos":"N","occurrence_count":9},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14847","n14851","n14852","n14853"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%AC%D9%8E%D8%B2%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14847","headword_ar":"رَجِزَ","root":"rjz","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] (S,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajazN","text_ar":"رَجَزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a camel)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had the disease termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajazN","text_ar":"رَجَزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[expl. below]. (S.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaza","text_ar":"رَجَزَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajozN","text_ar":"رَجْزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He said, spoke, uttered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recited, poetry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"verse, of the metre termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajazN","text_ar":"رَجَزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [see this word below;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he spoke in verse of that metre; he poetized,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"versified, in that metre;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Artjz","text_ar":"ارتجز","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, * Msb, K, * TA;) and in like manner ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Arjz","text_ar":"ارجز","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he composed verses of that metre."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-Buzurj, L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qSd","text_ar":"قصد"},{"kind":"text","text":".) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajazabihi","text_ar":"رَجَزَبِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He recited to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ano$adahu","text_ar":"اَنْشَدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so in more than one MS. copy of the K, and in the TA, but in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ano$ada","text_ar":"اَنْشَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", without the affixed pronoun, which is probably wrong,])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a poem of that metre;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rj~zhu","text_ar":"رجّزهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarojiyzN","text_ar":"تَرْجِيزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trj~z","text_ar":"ترجّز","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He urged,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excited, his camels by singing"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaz","text_ar":"رَجَز"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaz","text_ar":"رَجَز"},{"kind":"text","text":": so accord. to different copies of the K. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajazati Alr~iyHu","text_ar":"رَجَزَتِ الرِّيحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajozN","text_ar":"رَجْزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wind was continuous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lasting."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~aEodu","text_ar":"الرَّعْدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Artjz","text_ar":"ارتجز","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The thunder made uninterrupted sounds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"like the recitation of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAjiz","text_ar":"رَاجِز"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A, TA:) or, as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trj~z","text_ar":"ترجّز","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made a sound:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made consecutive sounds."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baA=*iy~ihi","text_ar":"بَا=ذِيِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaHoru yarotajizu","text_ar":"البَحْرُ يَرْتَجِزُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sea makes a continuous sound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"murmuring, with its waves"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yataraj~azu","text_ar":"يَتَرَجَّزُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, TA.) [And hence, perhaps,] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trj~z","text_ar":"ترجّز","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~aHaAbu","text_ar":"السَّحَابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The clouds moved slowly by reason of the abundance of their water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) [See also 6.]"}],"source_refs":["S","TA","Msb","K","A"]},{"entry_id":"n14851","headword_ar":"رُجْزٌ","root":"rjz","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next paragraph, in four places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n14852","headword_ar":"رِجْزٌ","root":"rjz","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"properly signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Commotion, agitation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"convulsion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consecutiveness of motions."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  Hence, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Punishment"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Is-hák, S, Mgh, Msb, K) [like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijosN","text_ar":"رِجْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that agitates by its vehemence, and occasions vehement consecutive commotions;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Is-hák, Mgh, * TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rujozN","text_ar":"رُجْزٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) so in the Kur vii. 131; (Aboo-Is-hák;) and in ii. 56, and vii. 162, and xxix. 33. (S.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Conduct that leads to punishment:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so, accord. to some, in the Kur lxxiv. 5; (TA;) where some read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ijoza","text_ar":"الرِّجْزَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and others ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ujoza","text_ar":"الرُّجْزَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, TA:) ↓ the latter is also expl. as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sin:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and both,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uncleanness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"filth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) so in that instance: like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijosN","text_ar":"رِجْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"polytheism;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"associating of another, or others, with the true God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) so, accord to some, in that instance: because he who worships what is not God is in doubt respecting his case, and unsettled in his belief: (TA:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"worship of idols:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) so, accord. to some, in the same instance: (TA:) or the meaning there is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and idol:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mujáhid, S:) or ↓ the latter word signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain idol;"},{"kind":"text","text":"being the name thereof: (Katádeh, TA:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"devil:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his suggestions."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Plague,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pestilence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAEuwnN","text_ar":"طَاعُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","K","S"]},{"entry_id":"n14853","headword_ar":"رَجَزٌ","root":"rjz","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain disease which attacks camels, in the rump;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that when a she-camel rises, or is roused, her thighs tremble for a while, and then stretch out:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is when there is a convulsive motion in the hind leg or the thighs of a camel, when he desires to stand up, or rises, or is roused, for a while, and then a stretching out of the same."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-  Hence, (S,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ajazu","text_ar":"الرَّجَزُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain species"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of verse"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poetry;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the metres of verse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consisting of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musotafoEiluno","text_ar":"مُسْتَفْعِلُنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"primarily"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"six times:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) a metre easy to the ear and impressive to the mind; wherefore it may be reduced to a single hemistich, and also to two feet instead of six: (TA:) so called because it commences with a motion and a quiescence, [i. e., a movent and a quiescent letter,] followed by a motion and a quiescence; and so in the other feet; resembling the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaz","text_ar":"رَجَز"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a she-camel, which consists in her quivering and then being quiet: (TA:) or because of the contractedness of its feet, and the fewness of its letters: (S, K:) or because it is [characterized by]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Suduwr","text_ar":"صُدُور"},{"kind":"text","text":"without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEojaAz","text_ar":"اَعْجَاز"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit. breasts without rumps; for, as the two hemistichs generally rhyme with each other, the verse seems as though it had no"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eajuz","text_ar":"عَجُز"},{"kind":"text","text":"; i. e., as though its last foot should rather be called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaruwDN","text_ar":"عَرُوضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like the last of the first hemistich, than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EajuzN","text_ar":"عَجُزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] (TA:) Akh once said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajazN","text_ar":"رَجَزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with the Arabs, is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whatever consists of three feet;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and it is that [kind of verse] which they sing in their work, and in driving their camels: [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi*olapN","text_ar":"بِذْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence:] ISd says that certain of those in whom he placed confidence related this on the authority of Kh. (TA.) Some say that it is not verse, or poetry, but a kind of rhyming prose; but Kh held it to be true verse, or poetry: so in the M: but in the T it is said [as in the K] that Kh asserted it to be not poetry, but halves or thirds of verses: one of his reasons for this assertion [the only one that seems to have had much weight with the Muslims] is, that Mo- hammad once said,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^anaA A@bonu Eabodi AlmuT~alibo \n                      \n                     \n                        A^anaA Aln~abiY~u laA ka*ibo"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is an instance of a species of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaz","text_ar":"رَجَز"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning, “ I am the Prophet: it is no lie: I am the son of 'Abd-el-Muttalib ”]: and were this verse, he would not have said it, as is shown by what is said in the Kur., xxxvi. 69: but on this point, Akh has contended against him. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}